#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.48"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.48:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.48:0.2"
msgid "5. Muṇḍarājavagga"
msgstr "5. With King Muṇḍa"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.48:0.3"
msgid "48. Alabbhanīyaṭhānasutta"
msgstr "48. Things That Cannot Be Had"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.48:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, alabbhanīyāni ṭhānāni samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā "
"devena vā mārena vā brahmunā vā kenaci vā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, there are five things that cannot be had by any ascetic or "
"brahmin or god or Māra or Brahmā or by anyone in the world."

msgctxt "an5.48:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.48:1.3"
msgid ""
"‘Jarādhammaṃ mā jīrī’ti alabbhanīyaṃ ṭhānaṃ samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā devena "
"vā mārena vā brahmunā vā kenaci vā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "That someone liable to old age should not grow old."

msgctxt "an5.48:1.4"
msgid ""
"‘Byādhidhammaṃ mā byādhīyī’ti … pe … ‘maraṇadhammaṃ mā mīyī’ti … ‘"
"khayadhammaṃ mā khīyī’ti … ‘nassanadhammaṃ mā nassī’ti alabbhanīyaṃ ṭhānaṃ "
"samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā devena vā mārena vā brahmunā vā kenaci vā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"That someone liable to sickness should not get sick. … That someone liable "
"to death should not die. … That someone liable to ending should not end. … "
"That someone liable to perishing should not perish. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.48:2.1"
msgid "Assutavato, bhikkhave, puthujjanassa jarādhammaṃ jīrati."
msgstr ""
"An uneducated ordinary person has someone liable to old age who grows old."

msgctxt "an5.48:2.2"
msgid "So jarādhamme jiṇṇe na iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "But they don’t reflect:"

#. VAR: mayhevekassa → mayhamevekassa (bj)
msgctxt "an5.48:2.3"
msgid ""
"‘na kho mayhevekassa jarādhammaṃ jīrati, atha kho yāvatā sattānaṃ āgati gati "
"cuti upapatti sabbesaṃ sattānaṃ jarādhammaṃ jīrati."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s not just me who has someone liable to old age who grows old. For as "
"long as sentient beings come and go, die and are reborn, they all have "
"someone liable to old age who grows old."

#. VAR: Ahañceva → ahañce (?)
#. VAR: kammantāpi nappavatteyyuṃ → kammantopi nappavatteyya (mr)
msgctxt "an5.48:2.4"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana jarādhamme jiṇṇe soceyyaṃ kilameyyaṃ parideveyyaṃ, "
"urattāḷiṃ kandeyyaṃ, sammohaṃ āpajjeyyaṃ, bhattampi me nacchādeyya, kāyepi "
"dubbaṇṇiyaṃ okkameyya, kammantāpi nappavatteyyuṃ, amittāpi attamanā assu, "
"mittāpi dummanā assū’ti."
msgstr ""
"If I were to sorrow and pine and lament, beating my breast and falling into "
"confusion, just because someone liable to old age grows old, I’d lose my "
"appetite and my body would become ugly. My work wouldn’t get done, my "
"enemies would be encouraged, and my friends would be dispirited.’"

msgctxt "an5.48:2.5"
msgid ""
"So jarādhamme jiṇṇe socati kilamati paridevati, urattāḷiṃ kandati, sammohaṃ "
"āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"And so, when someone liable to old age grows old, they sorrow and pine and "
"lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion."

msgctxt "an5.48:2.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave:"
msgstr "This is called"

msgctxt "an5.48:2.7"
msgid ""
"‘assutavā puthujjano viddho savisena sokasallena attānaṃyeva paritāpeti’."
msgstr ""
"an uneducated ordinary person struck by sorrow’s poisoned arrow, who only "
"mortifies themselves."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.55"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
